                                .card.getting-started-sec
                                  .card-body.p-0
                                    .alert-box.alert.alert-primary.mb-0
                                            p.mt-0 Cuba React Admin Theme is pure React theme, Yes! you read correct, it's 
                                              b No Jquery React admin theme 
                                              | including all feature and functionality with ease of integration for your project.Cuba theme document will help you to understand React from scratch to making perfect real time dream application.
                                            hr
                                            p We also includes 
                                              b React Hooks 
                                              | and 
                                              b Redux 
                                              | which is manage applications data in easy way. It's user freindlly to learn the application.
                                            p Follow the documentation carefully for solving your issues in minutes, Apart from that if you don't find solution when you following the docs you can raise a support ticket for your issue from 
                                              a(href="https://pixelstrap.freshdesk.com" target="_blank") 
                                                b pixelstrap.freshdesk.com
                                .card.gulp-section
                                  .card-header
                                    h4.mb-0 How to start
                                  .card-body
                                    p Welcome to React! React helps you build modern applications for the web, mobile, or desktop.
                                    p.mb-4 For getting started an React application you needs two things as Prerequisites.
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Prerequisites
                                    ul
                                      li 
                                        p.mb-4 Before you begin, make sure your development environment includes 
                                          b Node 
                                          | and an 
                                          b npm package manager.
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Node.js
                                    ul
                                      li 
                                        p Download latest version of node.js from 
                                          a(href="https://nodejs.org" target='_blank')
                                            b nodejs.org.
                                      li
                                        p Install Node.js using downloaded file 
                                      li 
                                        p.mb-4 To check your node version, run 
                                          b node -v 
                                          | in a terminal/console window.
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Npm package manager
                                    ul
                                      li 
                                        p React CLI, and React apps depend on features and functionality provided by libraries that are available as npm packages. To download and install npm packages, you must have an 
                                          a(href="https://www.npmjs.com" target='_blank') 
                                            b npm 
                                          | package manager.
                                      li
                                        p This Quick Start uses the npm client command line interface, which is installed with Node.js by default. To check that you have the npm client installed, run 
                                          b npm -v 
                                          | in a terminal/console window.
                                      li
                                        p For better understanding React we suggest you to once go through official documentation of React from 
                                          a(href="https://reactjs.org/docs/getting-started.html" target='_blank') 
                                            b ReactJS.org
                                .card.gulp-section
                                  .card-header
                                    h4.mb-0 React setup
                                  .card-body
                                    .warning-block.mb-4
                                      p If you want Cuba theme setup then directly follow next Cuba setup section
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Installing React CLI
                                    ul.mb-4
                                      li 
                                        p You use the React CLI to create projects, generate application and library code, and perform a variety of ongoing development tasks as it is a progressive framework for building user interfaces.
                                      li
                                        p Install the React CLI globally.
                                      li 
                                        p To install the CLI using npm, open a terminal/console window and enter the following command:
                                        .code-box-copy
                                              button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#installcode1' title='Copy')
                                                i.fa.fa-files-o
                                              pre
                                                code#installcode1.language-html
                                                  | npm install -g create-react-app
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Create Initial application 
                                    ul.list-none 
                                      li 1. Run the CLI command react create and provide the name my-app, as shown here:
                                        .py-2.ps-3
                                          .code-box-copy
                                                button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#createcode1' title='Copy')
                                                  i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                pre
                                                  code#createcode1.language-html
                                                    | npm create-react-app my-app
                                      li 2.  The react create command prompts you for information about features to include in the initial app project. Accept the defaults by pressing the Enter or Return key.
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Run Application
                                    ul.list-none
                                      li 1. Go to the workspace folder (my-app).
                                        .py-2.ps-3
                                          .code-box-copy
                                                button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#cdcode' title='Copy')
                                                  i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                pre
                                                  code#cdcode.language-html
                                                    | cd my-app
                                      li 2. Launch the server by using the CLI command npm start
                                        .py-2.ps-3
                                          .code-box-copy
                                                button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#npmcode' title='Copy')
                                                  i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                pre
                                                  code#npmcode.language-html
                                                    | npm start
                                    a(href="https://reactjs.org/docs/create-a-new-react-app.html" target='_blank').btn.btn-solid Supplemental
                                .card.gulp-section
                                  .card-header
                                    h4.mb-0 Cuba setup
                                  .card-body
                                    p.mb-4 If you have already download and install node.js and React CLI then ignore prerequisites accordingly.
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 Node.js
                                    ul
                                      li 
                                        p Download latest version of node.js from 
                                          a(href="https://nodejs.org" target='_blank')
                                            b nodejs.org.
                                      li
                                        p Install Node.js using downloaded file 
                                      li 
                                        p.mb-4 To check your node version, run 
                                          b node -v 
                                          | in a terminal/console window.
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3 React CLI
                                    ul
                                      li Install React CLI Using:
                                        .code-box-copy
                                              button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#installcode2' title='Copy')
                                                i.fa.fa-files-o
                                              pre
                                                code#installcode2.language-html
                                                  | npm install -g create-react-app
                                    h6.text-primary.mb-3.pt-2
                                      i(data-feather='arrow-right') 
                                      | Setup Cuba theme by
                                    ul.list-none
                                      li 1) Download and extract an Cuba themes from themeforest
                                      li 2) Extract it and then go in to theme folder.
                                        .py-2.ps-3
                                          .code-box-copy
                                                button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#cdcode2' title='Copy')
                                                  i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                pre
                                                  code#cdcode2.language-html
                                                    | cd theme
                                      li 3)  Import all dependency by installing npm command
                                        .py-2.ps-3
                                          .code-box-copy
                                                button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#npmcode2' title='Copy')
                                                  i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                pre
                                                  code#npmcode2.language-html
                                                    | npm install
                                      li 4)  Now you are in stage to successfully run Cuba using below command:
                                        .py-2.ps-3
                                          .code-box-copy
                                                button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#npmcode3' title='Copy')
                                                  i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                pre
                                                  code#npmcode3.language-html
                                                    | npm start
                                          p Once you serve your application by default it will take their defalult port so you can open port using 
                                            a(href="javascript:void(0)") localhost://3000
                                          .warning-block.mb-2
                                            p Make sure you are not running any other react project in local if so then use new generated port from terminal with label called 
                                              b app running at:
                                          .dark-block.mb-4
                                            b Some Common solution if you do not run project successfully
                                            ul.mt-2.p-0 
                                              li.mb-1  Use Latest Version of node.js
                                              li.mb-1  Remove node_module and package-lock.json file and again do 
                                                b npm install
                                              li.mb-1  You can again download theme from themeforst and then again run
                                              li.mb-0  Then also if you don't solve issue you can generate a ticket.
                                          h6.text-primary.mb-3 Build Application
                                          ul.list-none
                                            li 1. Build you application for host on server using below command:
                                              .py-2.ps-3
                                                .code-box-copy
                                                      button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#buildcode1' title='Copy')
                                                        i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                      pre
                                                        code#buildcode1.language-html
                                                          | npm run build
                                            li 2. It will create one dist file in your theme folder. Make zip of dist folder. so here you are ready to upload your theme on server.
                                              p If youâ€™re using Apache HTTP Server, you need to create a .htaccess file in the public folder by pastng below code
                                              .py-2.ps-3
                                                .code-box-copy
                                                      button.code-box-copy__btn.btn-clipboard(data-clipboard-target='#buildcode2' title='Copy')
                                                        i.fa.fa-files-o
                                                      pre
                                                        code#buildcode2.language-html
                                                          | Options -MultiViews
                                                          | RewriteEngine On
                                                          | RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
                                                          | RewriteRule ^ index.html [QSA,L]
                                            li.mb-3 Now upload your dist folder on public folder
                                            li 
